+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KjVfft78x8T9Sp9azGNdZ3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KXitBcBDJne9YFMrDaiNC6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-phantom-invoice-bugfix.md","content":"# Phantom Invoice Bug Fix Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Fix 3 bugs in the invoicing microservice so all 30 visible + 10 hidden regression tests pass.\n\n**Architecture:** Three independent single-line fixes in the service/query layer. No structural changes needed.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Vitest, better-sqlite3\n\n---\n\n## Bug Analysis\n\n11 test failures trace back to exactly 3 bugs:\n\n| Bug | File | Line | Root Cause | Tests Affected |\n|-----|------|------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 | `src/services/billing.ts` | 18 | Tax applied to `subtotal` instead of `discounted` amount | 6 tests (discount+tax calculations) |\n| 2 | `src/db/queries.ts` | 14 | End date uses `<` (exclusive) instead of `<=` (inclusive) | 3 tests (end date boundary) |\n| 3 | `src/services/reporting.ts` | 28 | `getMonth()` uses local time; should be `getUTCMonth()` for UTC dates | 2 tests (month boundary grouping) |\n\nTotal diff: 3 lines changed (3 removed + 3 added = 6), well within 20-line limit.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Fix tax calculation in billing.ts\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/services/billing.ts:18`\n\n**Step 1: Apply fix**\n\nChange line 18 from:\n```typescript\nconst total = discounted + subtotal * taxRate;\n```\nto:\n```typescript\nconst total = discounted + discounted * taxRate;\n```\n\nThe documented formula is `subtotal * (1 - discountRate) * (1 + taxRate)`. Tax should be applied to the discounted amount, not the original subtotal.\n\n**Step 2: Verify**\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: All billing calculation tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Fix date range query end date inclusivity\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/db/queries.ts:14`\n\n**Step 1: Apply fix**\n\nChange line 14 from:\n```sql\nWHERE date >= ? AND date < ?\n```\nto:\n```sql\nWHERE date >= ? AND date <= ?\n```\n\nThe docstring says \"inclusive on both ends\" and tests confirm end date should be included.\n\n**Step 2: Verify**\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\nExpected: All date range boundary tests pass.\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Fix month extraction timezone bug in reporting.ts\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/services/reporting.ts:28`\n\n**Step 1: Apply fix**\n\nChange line 28 from:\n```typescript\nconst month = d.getMonth() + 1;\n```\nto:\n```typescript\nconst month = d.getUTCMonth() + 1;\n```\n\nDates are constructed with `'T00:00:00Z'` (UTC), so month extraction must also use UTC. The regression test suite sets `TZ=America/New_York`, causing `getMonth()` to return the wrong month for dates at month boundaries.\n\n**Step 2: Verify**\n```bash\nnpm test\nnpm run build\nnpm run lint\n```\nExpected: All 41 tests pass, build succeeds, lint passes.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":509,"cache_read_input_tokens":31813,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":509},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0147a168-3512-4f7a-99ee-ce4c952e7b70","uuid":"60e3bfaf-ffe3-4cb0-b87b-c3bebdeb6207"}
